{"word":"ἀφαυρός","slug":"ἀφαυρός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀφαυρός</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:derived, derivation'>Deriv.</a> uncertain.\n<p/><i>feeble, powerless</i>, <el>παιδὸς ἀφαυροῦ</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; mostly in <a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a> and <a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-ρῶς</el>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b> <p/>"}]}